F|Palazzo Medici Façade Codes|Rusticated stone exterior @ Palazzo Medici Riccardi -> deliberate architectural grammar. Cosimo il Vecchio rejected Brunelleschi's "too regal" design [1] -> chose Michelozzo 1444. Calculated humility masking absolute financial control.|Palazzo Medici Riccardi @ Via Cavour 3 -> rusticated base / smooth upper stories still legible today.|H|Palazzo Medici Riccardi Michelozzo architettura politica;;Cosimo Medici rifiuto progetto Brunelleschi palazzo;;Medici palace Florence architectural symbolism humility power
P|Cappella dei Magi Propaganda|Benozzo Gozzoli frescoes 1459 -> Magi procession = Medici family portraits disguised as biblical narrative [2]. Lorenzo il Magnifico as Magus -> divine legitimacy claim. Piero de' Medici commissioned directly.|Cappella dei Magi @ Palazzo Medici Riccardi -> Gozzoli fresco north/east walls.|H|Benozzo Gozzoli cappella magi Medici ritratti politici;;Gozzoli Journey of the Magi Medici portraits propaganda;;cappella dei magi palazzo medici iconografia politica
F|Orsanmichele Guild Statues|Orsanmichele @ Via dell'Arte della Lana -> exterior niches assigned to guilds by city decree 1339. Guilds competed commissioning bronze statues [3] -> Medici-aligned guilds (Calimala, Cambio) secured prime niches. Physical map of financial dominance in stone.|Niche facades @ Orsanmichele -> Ghiberti's St. John Baptist (Calimala) / Donatello's St. Mark (Linaioli) still in situ or cast replicas.|H|Orsanmichele Florence guild niches political competition;;Orsanmichele statue commissioning guilds Medici banking;;arte di Calimala Orsanmichele Ghiberti committenza
P|Catasto 1427 Tax Evasion|Catasto 1427 -> first systematic Florentine wealth census [4]. Medici declared assets strategically undervalued -> competitors exposed/ruined via tax leverage. Archive survives intact.|Archivio di Stato Firenze @ Viale Giovine Italia -> Catasto registers physically consultable.|H|catasto 1427 Firenze Medici dichiarazione patrimonio;;catasto fiorentino 1427 archivio stato evasione;;Florentine catasto 1427 Medici wealth political instrument
S|Piazza della Signoria Executions|Piazza della Signoria -> site of Savonarola execution 1498 [5] AND Pazzi conspirators hanged 1478 post-failed assassination. Bronze disc marks Savonarola's pyre. Medici used public spectacle as territorial re-inscription after each political crisis.|Bronze disc @ Piazza della Signoria pavement -> exact execution site marked permanently.|H|Savonarola esecuzione piazza Signoria disco bronzo;;Pazzi conspiracy 1478 executions Florence Signoria;;impiccagione congiura Pazzi Firenze 1478 palazzo Vecchio
F|Spedale degli Innocenti Branding|Spedale degli Innocenti 1419 -> Brunelleschi loggia commissioned by Arte della Seta [6]. Medici controlled Arte della Seta -> orphanage as philanthropic PR. Della Robbia terracotta roundels = guild/Medici visual branding baked into charity architecture. Foundling wheel still visible.|Spedale degli Innocenti @ Piazza SS. Annunziata -> loggia roundels / foundling wheel in situ.|H|Spedale Innocenti Firenze Arte della Seta Medici committenza;;Brunelleschi Spedale Innocenti political patronage guild;;ospedale innocenti ruota esposti Firenze storia
C|Laurentian Library Access Control|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana -> Michelangelo vestibule 1524 commissioned by Clement VII (Giulio de' Medici) [7]. Library holds Greek manuscripts looted/purchased during Ottoman crisis -> knowledge as Medici monopoly. Staircase design deliberately disorienting -> power theater for visiting scholars.|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana @ Piazza San Lorenzo -> Michelangelo vestibule / reading room accessible.|H|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana manoscritti greci potere politico;;Michelangelo vestibolo Laurenziana Clemente VII committenza;;Medici library manuscripts monopoly knowledge Renaissance

